Long name: eastward surface stress from planetary boundary layer scheme
description: The  downward eastward stress associated with the models parameterization of the plantary boundary layer. (This request is related to a WGNE effort to understand how models parameterize the surface stresses.)

Long name: northward surface stress from planetary boundary layer scheme
description: The  downward northward stress associated with the models parameterization of the plantary boundary layer. (This request is related to a WGNE effort to understand how models parameterize the surface stresses.)

Simulated reflectance from PARASOL as seen at the top of the atmosphere for 5 solar zenith angles. Valid only over ocean and for one viewing direction (viewing zenith angle of 30 degrees and relative azimuth angle 320 degrees).
cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
